---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import LessonShell from "../../components/LessonShell.astro";
import Reveal from "../../components/Reveal.astro";
import { LESSONS } from "../../data/curriculum";

const lesson = LESSONS.find((l) => l.id === "cowork-flow")!;
---

<Layout title={`${lesson.title} · Learn Claude`}>
  <main>
    <LessonShell lesson={lesson}>
      <p>
        The Cowork flow is a loop you'll do many times a day once it clicks. Submit, wait, review, decide.
      </p>

      <h2>The four steps</h2>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li><strong>Pick a repo and write the prompt.</strong> One task, one outcome. "Add a dark-mode toggle in the header." Keep the scope small enough that you'd trust an intern to finish it in an afternoon.</li>
        <li><strong>Submit and step away.</strong> Cowork checks the code out into its own sandbox and starts working. There's no live chat — it just runs.</li>
        <li><strong>Get a diff back.</strong> Usually within minutes for small tasks. You'll see the file changes, the test runs, and a short summary of what was done.</li>
        <li><strong>Decide.</strong> Three options: merge, comment back ("looks good but rename the variable"), or discard.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Writing a good task prompt</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <p style="margin-top: 0;"><strong>Three ingredients:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>The outcome.</strong> What does "done" look like?</li>
          <li><strong>Any constraints.</strong> "Don't touch the API". "Match the existing style of the settings page."</li>
          <li><strong>How to verify.</strong> "Tests should still pass." "I should be able to click the toggle and see the colours switch."</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2>A real example, written out</h2>
      <blockquote class="callout" style="font-style: italic;">
        "On the login page, the error message ('Invalid credentials') is currently red and very small. Make it the same size as the input labels and add a small warning icon to the left of the text. Match the icon style used elsewhere in the app — there's probably a Lucide or Heroicons import already. Don't change any of the auth logic. Tests should still pass."
      </blockquote>

      <h2>What Cowork is great at — and not</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Great at:</strong> small features, bug fixes, refactors with a clear before/after, dependency upgrades, adding tests, documentation passes.</li>
        <li><strong>Less great at:</strong> "design this product", architectural debates, anything where you'd want to argue back and forth. Use Claude.ai or Claude Code for those.</li>
      </ul>

      <Reveal q="What if it goes the wrong way?">
        Comment on the diff and Cowork iterates — same as a normal code review. Or close it and start over with a clearer prompt.
      </Reveal>
      <Reveal q="Can multiple tasks touch the same file?">
        Yes — each task runs on its own branch. If two PRs end up overlapping, you'll resolve the conflict at merge time, just like with humans.
      </Reveal>
    </LessonShell>
  </main>
</Layout>
